<item>
            <title>[LU-14063] fix reporting of client distro</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14063</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, a lot of test results in Maloo are reported with &quot;Client distro: CentOS 7.0&quot;, when they are actually CentOS7.7 or 7.8.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This appears to caused by the preference for &lt;tt&gt;/etc/os-release&lt;/tt&gt;, which only reports &quot;&lt;tt&gt;Version: 7 (Core)&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;, while &lt;tt&gt;/etc/centos-release&lt;/tt&gt; reports &quot;CentOS 7.7.1908 (Core)&quot; and should be used instead I think.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="61310">LU-14063</key>
            <summary>fix reporting of client distro</summary>
